<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="sick-adj">sick <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /sɪk/    美 /sɪk/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>有病的；患病的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>get</strong> / become <strong>sick</strong>
生病</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He has been <strong>on sick leave</strong> for three days.
他休病假已经三天了。</p></div>

<h3 id="ill-sick">辨析 ill, sick</h3>
<p>二者均含 “生病的”之意。<br />
<strong>ill</strong> 意为“生病的”时，只能作表语，而sick 既可作表语也可作定语。</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He has been ill / sick for ten days. 
他病了十天了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She is taking care of her sick child. 
她正在照顾生病的孩子。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>恶心的；要呕吐的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I <strong>am</strong> always <strong>sick</strong> in the car.
我经常晕车。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>[口语] 厌倦的；厌恶的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I was growing <strong>sick of</strong> my life in San Francisco.
我对在旧金山的生活愈发厌倦。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="be-worried-sick">(be) worried sick</h3>
<p>1.<strong>极度担心；担心得要命：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We have been worried sick about you. Are you okay?
我们非常担心你，你还好吗？</p></div></div>